addAsset(string,uint32,string,string).details: other asset struct members should be added

params.assetDescription: Descrption of the asset entered by owner
params.availablityDate: the first date the owner can donate the asset
params.imageIPFSHash: IPFS hash of the asset image uploaded by owner and saved to IPFS
params.location: the location of the donated asset

params.donorAddress: The address of donor to be approved

params.receiverAddress: The address of receiver to be approved

baseURI().details: Returns the base URI set via {_setBaseURI}. This will be automatically added as a prefix in {tokenURI} to each token's URI, or to the token ID if no specific URI is set for that token ID.

params.assetId: unique id of asset to be donated

getAllDonations().details: There must be better way than returing always an array of 16

returns._0: Asset returns an array of type asset and length 16 of all donations

getDonationsByOwner().details: There must be better way than returing always an array of 16

returns._0: Asset returns an array of type asset and length 16 of donations of msg.sender

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}.     * To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive.     * Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point.     * WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`.     * If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event.     * Requirements:     * - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

params.assetOwner: the owner of the new asset

returns._0: returns the id of new minted token

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account.     * Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced).     * If the calling account had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event.     * Requirements:     * - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`.     * If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event.     * Requirements:     * - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: See {IERC165-supportsInterface}.     * Time complexity O(1), guaranteed to always use less than 30 000 gas.

addAsset(string,uint32,string,string).notice: Adds a new asset to list of donated assets(Should be called by a donor)

addReceiver().notice: Adds an address to list of receivers

approveDonor(address).notice: Admin approves an address to have the donor role

approveReceiver(address).notice: Admin approves an address to have the receiver role

donateAsset(uint32,address).notice: a donor can approve a specific request and this function assigns the recipient of this asset to the recipientAddresscaller should be a donor and recipient should be a receiver

getDonationsByOwner().notice: Returns all donations of an donor(it shoud be called by a donor)

mintToken(address).notice: The ERC721 stadard for nunfungible token is used to maintain ownership of assetseverytime a new token is minted based on current value of lastAssetId for assetOwner address, and then lastAssetId is increased

userdoc.notice: This contract facilitates donation of physical assets for specific periods of time between asset owners and receivers
